cs.DS, cs.NI, cs.CG, cs.SI, cs.AL

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a likely category as the paper proposes approximation algorithms for two optimization problems.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the problems are motivated by applications in wireless sensor networks.
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is another possible category as the problems involve points in the Euclidean plane and geometric concepts such as sensor radius and communication radius.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible category as the communication graph of the sensors is an important aspect of the problems.
- cs.AL (Computational Complexity) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on the complexity of the problems, but rather on approximation algorithms.
